profileAlternative.headline: Software Engineer & Full Stack Node.js Developer en Whyline
profileAlternative.summary:
Julian is a Software Engineer and Full Stack Web Developer from Rosario, Argentina. He has experience with Node.js, Express, Fastify, Typecript, MongoDB, AWS, Angular 4 and Vue.js. Currently experimenting with React.js, gRPC and Rust.

Julian is a motivated team-player who strives to develop meaningful projects that make a real-world impact. He always enjoys taking on new challenges.

positions.title: Full Stack Node.js Developer
positions.description:
I am a member of the Scrum App Team, in charge of the research, design and development of new internal features and requirements in the backend servers, used by more than 350.000 active users.

We work putting a deep focus on speed, performance and reliability, using the latests and cutting-edge Javascript technologies and stacks, such as Node.js, Angular.js, Fastify, MongoDB, AWS and gPRC.

positions.title: Freelance Full Stack Web Developer
positions.description: We are a group of 8 close friends and engineers, that work on their free time to create and implement the best solution to problems and issues that people are having. We mostly work with the MEAN Stack (Node.js, Angular.js, MongoDB and Express), Laravel 5 and React Native.

positions.title: Laravel 5 and Vue.js Developer
positions.description: In charge of the development of a lite-CRM system used to manage 5000 customers and the services offered. Designed and launched an interacting site were potential customers can request the services and send inquiries.
